Print a sequence of numbers starting with n, without using a loop. Replace n with n - 5, nâˆ’5... until nâ‰¤0. Then, replace n with n+5, n + 5, n+5 until n regains its initial value. 
Complete the function pattern(n) which takes n as input and returns a list containing the pattern.

def pattern(self,n):
  num=n
  ans=[]
  ans.append(n)
  while n>0:
    n-=5
    ans.append(n)
  if n!=num:
    n+=5
    ans.append(n)
  return ans
    
    
    
